SIMPLE: promiscuous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Promiscuous
<hw>Pro*mis"cu*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>promiscuus</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> before, in place of, for +
<ets>miscere</ets> to mix. See <er>Mix</er>. ]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting of individuals united in a body or mass
without order; mingled; confused; undistinguished; <as>as, a
<ex>promiscuous</ex> crowd or mass</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A wild, where weeds and flowers <qex>promiscuous</qex> shoot.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Distributed or applied without order or
discrimination; not restricted to an individual; common; indiscriminate;
<as>as, <ex>promiscuous</ex> love or intercourse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Promiscuously</ent>⟦br⟧
